                        syriaca-computed-end="0552">0540-0552</floruit>
               <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bibl306-1">Textes dans Bedjan, Jab-Alaha, 206- 74 ; BHO, 595. P. Peeters, "Observations sur Ia Vie syriaque de Mar Aba", dans RHPO, II, 116- 63. BSO, I, 1- 4 (J .M. Fiey).</quote>
               </note>
               <note type="abstract">Catholicos Aba I is a widely venerated saint in the Church of the East.  He was a reformer, theologian, Confessor, and a Zoroastrian convert, and student of the School of Nisibis.  He wrote against the practices of the Zoroastrians.             </note>
